sentences: Anne Evans (January 23, 1871 – January 6, 1941) was an American arts patron.
She had decades of experience in leadership positions, particularly in the field of art.
Anne Evans was inducted into both the Colorado Business Hall of Fame and the Colorado Women's Hall of Fame in 2016.
Anne Evans was born on January 23, 1871 in London, England.
She received an honorary doctorate of fine arts degree from the University of Denver in 1939.
Evans joined the Denver Artists' Club in 1893, as did her mother, Margaret Gray Evans.
While she studied at the Art Students League of New York, she began to serve the club's governing council in 1896.
She was a member of the board beginning in 1896.
She then was on the board of the Denver Art Museum beginning in 1923, when it was incorporated, until 1931.
